parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stabilitrak and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak and Traction Control System can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The Stabilitrak warning light comes on
the traction control light comes on
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the engine stalls
and the vehicle may shut off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or won't start
and the ignition switch is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of essential systems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The dashboard lights flicker
the radio turns on and off
the doors lock and unlock randomly
and the vehicle experiences electrical failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear defroster can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear defroster does not work
and the connector is burned or melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrack system and engine power reduction can cause the vehicle to lose power and stability, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Stabilitrack Service Light" comes on
the "Check Engine Light" comes on
a message for "reduced engine power" appears
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle's stability is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Seat Headrests Obstructing Rear View
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear seat headrests can obstruct the driver's view of the rear window, making it difficult to see behind the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries when backing up or changing lanes.
symptoms: The rear seat headrests block a significant portion of the rear window
making it difficult to see other vehicles
pedestrians
or objects behind the vehicle
especially when using the rearview mirror.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: StabilTrak and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the StabilTrak and Traction Control System can cause the vehicle to lose power, reducing engine speed and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The StabilTrak light and/or Traction Control light come on
accompanied by a message indicating "Service StabilTrak" or "Service Traction Control"
and/or "Engine Power Reduced". The vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power
stuttering
or jerking
and may be unable to accelerate or maintain speed.
